'''Facundo Pellistri Rebollo''' ({{IPA|es|faˈkundo peˈlistɾi}}; born 20 December 2001) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Super League Greece|Greek Super League]] club [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

Born in [[Montevideo]], Pellistri is a graduate of [[Peñarol]]'s youth system. He made 37 first-team appearances for the club and was named in the [[Uruguayan Primera División]] Team of the Season in 2019. He transferred to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in October 2020, for a fee of £9 million. After joining United, he had two loan spells at Spanish club [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]], where he made 35 appearances in total, before a further loan spell at fellow La Liga side Granada in 2024. He joined Panathinaikos F.C. for a fee of around £5.1 million in August 2024.

Pellistri represented Uruguay at under-16 level, before making his senior international debut in January 2022. He played for Uruguay at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Early life and education==
Pellistri was born on 20 December 2001 in the capital city of [[Montevideo]] to a family of [[Spanish Uruguayans|Spanish]] and [[Italian Uruguayans|Italian]] descent. His father, Marcelo, is an [[accountant]] and his mother, Lucía (née Rebollo), is a [[pediatrician]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last=Mitten |first=Andy |date=2021-10-11 |title=Facundo Pellistri: 'My baby-like signature almost cost me my move to Manchester United' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2880125/2021/10/10/facundo-pellistri-my-baby-like-signature-almost-cost-me-my-move-to-manchester-united/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Along with his native Uruguayan passport, Pellistri also has a [[Spanish passport]] through his father's grandmother, a native of the municipality of [[A Coruña]] in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-04-28 |title=Pellistri, comunitario y en la mira del Real Madrid |url=https://www.tenfield.com.uy/pellistri-comunitario-y-en-la-mira-de-real-madrid/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=Tenfield.com |language=es}}</ref> The lead singer of Uruguayan rock band [[La Vela Puerca]], Sebastián Teysera, is Pellistri's [[Godparent|godfather]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Emirona07 |date=2017-09-29 |title=Facundo Pellistri: "Hacer un gol clásico es único" |url=https://www.padreydecano.com/cms/formativas/facundo-pellistri-hacer-un-gol-clasico-es-unico/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=Padre y Decano - El Sitio del Pueblo |language=es}}</ref>

Pellistri was privately educated at two institutions in the [[Pocitos]] neighbourhood: St Brendan's School for his early years, where he first learned English, and then [[Ivy Thomas Memorial School]] for high school.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pellistri en su camino, entre Forlán y el Chino Recoba |url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/pellistri-en-su-camino-entre-forlan-y-el-chino-202010172260?__cf_chl_rt_tk=J3KDmBvLMzGaZQNDQ8fOJIObL3BEJxxfmQP.1z4RiaI-1743382289-1.0.1.1-2zDP9uxJUfsTFJqKdL0NrASUp6.nlRARxXs_iIcfYhE |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]] |language=es-UY}}</ref> His strongest subject at school was [[mathematics]]. In 2019, Pellistri graduated from a pre-architectural study program.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-11-25 |title=Facundo Pellistri: "Xisco me agarró y me dijo: 'el gol es tuyo'" |url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/ovacion/futbol/equipo/penarol/facundo-pellistri-xisco-me-agarro-y-me-dijo-el-gol-es-tuyo |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=EL PAIS |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
=== Peñarol ===
Facundo began his football career at the age of 4 at La Picada, a baby football club. Later, he had a brief stint with [[Club Atlético River Plate (Uruguay)|River Plate]] in AUFI, and since 2012, he has been playing in the youth divisions of [[Club Atlético Peñarol|Peñarol]], a club he supports.

His first three years at Peñarol were in AUFI. In 2015, he began to be part of the club's youth teams, starting with the U-14. In the Juveniles, he played 115 matches and scored 49 goals. He was part of the U-14, U-15, U-16, and U-17 teams.

In 2017, Pellistri won his first Uruguayan championship, obtaining the title in U-16 after defeating [[Defensor Sporting Club|Defensor Sporting]] 2-1 in the tournament final. That same year, he scored his first classic goal. The match corresponded to the 4th round of the Clausura Tournament, and near the end, he scored the goal that sealed the final result of the match (2-1). This match against [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]] was played at the [[Estadio Centenario]], a national historic monument, marking his first official game at that venue.

In 2018, the year in which Facundo was part of the U-17 team, he was called up for the first time to train with the main squad of the [[Club Atlético Peñarol|''carbonero'']], led by [[Luis Diego López|Diego López]], to carry out the mid-year preseason in the department of Colonia. At that time, the player was 16 years old and experiencing his first involvement with the main squad.

In 2019, the player alternated between the main squad and the reserves, where he played 13 matches. Finally, on August 11, 2019, he made his first division debut. He came on in the 89th minute against Defensor Sporting at the [[Estadio Luis Franzini]], during the 4th round of the Torneo Intermedio 2019. Although he had relatively few minutes on the field, in his first play, he managed to excite the fans. The match ended in a 2-2 draw.

From then on, Facundo began to be more frequently considered for the main squad. On November 6, 2019, he scored his first official goal in the first division, in a 3-1 victory against [[Club Atlético Cerro|Cerro]] during the 10th round of the Torneo Clausura 2019, held at the [[Estadio Luis Tróccoli]]. Since his debut, he started gaining more playing time and quickly ignited great excitement among Peñarol fans, to the point that just a few months after his debut, he was selected through various social media platforms of the [[Asociación Uruguaya de Fútbol|AUF]] as the public's player of the year 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Jugador del Público: Facundo Pellistri - AUF |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/jugador-del-publico-facundo-pellistri/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=www.auf.org.uy}}</ref> He was also distinguished as a member of the ideal team of the 2019 Uruguayan Championship, having participated in only 50% of the year's matches.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Equipo Ideal del Campeonato Uruguayo 2019 - AUF |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/equipo-ideal-del-campeonato-uruguayo-2019/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=www.auf.org.uy}}</ref>

But he didn't just excite and attract the interest of fans. Shortly after becoming a major revelation in the local scene, rumors began to surface from major global institutions. [[Club Atlético Boca Juniors|Boca Juniors]], [[Club Atlético de Madrid|Atlético de Madrid]], [[Arsenal Football Club|Arsenal]], [[Fútbol Club Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Real Madrid Club de Fútbol|Real Madrid]], and [[Manchester City Football Club|Manchester City]] were some of the clubs that reportedly showed interest in the player. In December 2019, [[Juan Román Riquelme]], vice president of Boca Juniors and former player of the club, publicly praised the player and stated that "''there are not many players like him anymore''".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Riquelme sobre Pellistri: "Se nota que es bastante sinvergüenza para jugar" |url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/riquelme-sobre-pellistri-se-nota-que-es-bastante-sinverguenza-para-jugar--20191229112319 |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=El Observador |language=es-UY}}</ref>

In February 2020, his contract with Peñarol was renewed until 2022, which included a release clause of 15 million dollars, a historic and significant amount for the institution.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-02-09 |title=Facundo Pellistri firmó por tres años con Peñarol |url=https://www.carasycaretas.com.uy/facundo-pellistri-firmo-por-tres-anos-con-penarol |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=www.carasycaretas.com.uy |language=es-ES}}</ref>

===Manchester United===
Pellistri joined Manchester United on 5 October 2020,<ref name=":2">{{cite news |date=5 October 2020 |title=Pellistri becomes a Red |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-sign-facundo-pellistri-from-club-atletico-penarol |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101020753/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-sign-facundo-pellistri-from-club-atletico-penarol |archive-date=1 November 2020 |access-date=5 October 2020 |website= |publisher=[[Manchester United FC]]}}</ref> for a reported transfer fee of £9 million, on a five-year contract.<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite news |date=2020-10-05 |title=Alex Telles: Man Utd sign Porto left-back and agree Amad Diallo move |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54425891 |access-date=2025-03-31 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-10-05 |title=Man Utd complete €10 million signing of Uruguayan star Pellistri {{!}} Goal.com English Qatar |url=https://www.goal.com/en-qa/news/man-utd-complete-10-million-signing-of-uruguayan-star/10at0l08wyrl61ni73unr44oya |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-QA}}</ref> [[Diego Forlán]], who was then managing Peñarol, endorsed Pellistri in a conversation with Manchester United manager and former teammate [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]], comparing the young player to [[Ryan Giggs]] and emphasizing his ability to speak English.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-10-16 |title=Diego Forlan reveals what he told Man Utd boss Solskjaer about Facundo Pellistri |url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/10/16/diego-forlan-reveals-what-he-told-ole-gunnar-solskjaer-about-manchester-new-boy-facundo-pellistri-13432417/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=Metro |language=en}}</ref> His first pre-season goal was on 18 July 2021, against [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]], in a 2–1 away win at [[Pride Park]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Derby 1 Manchester United 2 |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/derby-v-man-utd-friendly-match-report-18-july-2021 |website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=18 July 2021 |access-date=4 August 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Man United 2-1 Derby (18 Jul, 2021) Game Analysis - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/606658 |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

==== Loan to Alavés ====
On 31 January 2021, Pellistri joined [[Deportivo Alavés]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ganley |first=Joe |date=31 January 2021 |title=Facundo Pellistri joins Alaves on loan |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-winger-facundo-pellistri-completes-loan-move-to-alaves |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202110618/https://www.manutd.com/en/amp/news/detail/man-utd-winger-facundo-pellistri-completes-loan-move-to-alaves |archive-date=2 February 2021 |access-date=31 January 2021 |website= |publisher=Manchester United FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Booth |first=Dominic |date=2021-01-31 |title=Facundo Pellistri loan exit from Manchester United confirmed |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/facundo-pellistri-man-utd-breaking-19739427 |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=Manchester Evening News |language=en}}</ref> He returned to United to play in their summer pre-season matches, before going back on loan to Alavés in August for the 2021–22 season.<ref>{{cite news |last=Partington |first=Mikey |date=5 August 2021 |title=Loan move secured for Pellistri |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/facundo-pellistri-rejoins-deportivo-alaves-on-loan-for-the-2021-22-campaign-5-august-2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211007143139/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/facundo-pellistri-rejoins-deportivo-alaves-on-loan-for-the-2021-22-campaign-5-august-2021 |archive-date=7 October 2021 |accessdate=5 August 2021 |website= |publisher=Manchester United FC}}</ref>

==== 2022–23 season ====
Pellistri made his competitive debut for Manchester United on 10 January 2023, coming on as a substitute and assisting the second goal in a 3–0 [[2022–23 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] win over [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-01-09 |title=Manchester United 3-0 Charlton Athletic: Old Trafford side into Carabao Cup semi-finals |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64149053 |access-date=2025-03-31 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Pellistri made his Premier League debut on 8 February 2023, coming on as a substitute in a 2–2 draw against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/man-utd-vs-leeds-united-match-report-8-february-2023|title=Manchester United 2 Leeds United 2|work=Manchester United|date=9 February 2023|access-date=4 March 2023|last=Mulholland|first=Charlie}}</ref> On 17 March 2023, Pellistri made his first senior start for United, against [[Real Betis]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Marshall |first=Adam |date=17 March 2023 |title=Facundo Pellistri Watch On His First Senior Start for Man United |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/facundo-pellistri-watch-on-his-first-senior-start-for-man-united |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327063951/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/facundo-pellistri-watch-on-his-first-senior-start-for-man-united |archive-date=27 March 2023 |access-date=23 March 2023 |work=Manchester United FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Burt |first1=Jason |last2=Bagchi |first2=Rob |date=2023-03-16 |title=Real Betis vs Manchester United result: Marcus Rashford keeps post-World Cup scoring bandwagon rolling with wonder strike |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2023/03/16/real-betis-vs-manchester-united-live-europa-league-latest-updates/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref> On 20 September 2023, Pellistri made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], in the group stage, at [[Allianz Arena]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Manchester United: Breaking News, Rumors & Highlights |url=https://www.yardbarker.com/soccer/teams/manchester_united/17447 |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=Yardbarker |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Athletic |first=The |date=2023-09-20 |title=Garnacho and Martial on for United |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/bayern-munich-manchester-united-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/GrjE4z9ZG6jW/h7F1mHMTdb6O/ |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=The Athletic |language=en-US}}</ref>

==== Loan to Granada ====
On 31 January 2024, Pellistri joined [[Granada CF|Granada]] on a loan deal until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 January 2024 |title=Pellistri seals loan move to Granada |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/Facundo-Pellistri-seals-loan-move-to-Granada-in-La-Liga |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240203224435/https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/Facundo-Pellistri-seals-loan-move-to-Granada-in-La-Liga |archive-date=3 February 2024 |access-date=2024-02-01 |website=Manchester United FC |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 11 February, Pellistri netted his first goal for Granada in a La Liga game against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], which ended in a 3–3 stalemate.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Facundo Pellistri slots in the goal for Granada - Stream the Video - Watch ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/watch/player/_/id/39506189 |access-date=2025-03-31 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Barcelona held by Granada in six-goal thriller - as it happened |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/68220678 |access-date=2025-03-31 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Panathinaikos===
On 21 August 2024, Pellistri signed for [[Super League Greece]] club [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]] on a four-year deal.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.pao.gr/transfers/ston-panathinaiko-o-fakounto-pelistri/|trans-title=At Panathinaikos, Facundo Pelistri|title=Στον Παναθηναϊκό ο Φακούντο Πελίστρι|language=Greek|website=www.pao.gr|date=21 August 2024|accessdate=21 August 2024}}</ref> The fee was a reported €6 million (£5.1 million) with up to €2 million in performance based add-ons, with Manchester United also holding a 45% sell-on clause as well as a three-year buy-back option.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5711493/2024/08/21/facundo-pellistri-joins-panathinaikos/|title=Facundo Pellistri joins Panathinaikos|publisher=The Athletic|last=Whitwell|first=Laurie|date=21 August 2024|accessdate=21 August 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Facundo Pellistri 2022.jpg|thumb|221x221px|Pellistri lining up for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in 2022]]
Pellistri is a former Uruguayan youth international, having made two appearances at under-16 level in 2017.<ref name="debynt">{{cite web|title=Debutantes de la 4a fecha del Torneo Intermedio 2019|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/debutantes-de-la-4a-fecha-del-torneo-intermedio-2019/|date=14 August 2019|access-date=3 July 2021}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Uruguay national football team|senior team]] for the first time on 7 January 2022, for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifying]] matches against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] and [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Reservados vs. Paraguay y Venezuela|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/reservados-vs-paraguay-venezuela/|date=7 January 2022|access-date=7 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=January's international break explained |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/a-guide-to-the-january-2022-international-break-for-manchester-united-players|website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=26 January 2022|access-date=27 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Forlan preaches patience with Pellistri|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/diego-forlan-preaches-patience-with-loanee-facundo-pellistri|website=ManUtd.com |publisher=Manchester United |date=25 January 2022|access-date=27 January 2022}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 27 January, in a 1–0 away win against Paraguay.<ref>{{cite web|title=Facundo Pellistri makes debut for Uruguay in World Cup qualifying win |url=https://www.unitedinfocus.com/news/facundo-pellistri-makes-debut-for-uruguay-in-world-cup-qualifying-win/ |website=United in Focus |date=27 January 2022|access-date=27 January 2022}}</ref>

Pellistri was included in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Uruguay|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.auf.org.uy/se-confirmo-la-lista-de-convocados-para-la-copa-mundial-de-catar-2022/ |title=Se confirmó la lista de convocados para la Copa Mundial de Catar 2022 |trans-title=2022 Qatar World Cup squad confirmed |publisher=[[Uruguayan Football Association]] |date=10 November 2022 |access-date=10 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref> He started and played for 88 minutes in Uruguay's first game of the tournament, against [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]], before being replaced by [[Guillermo Varela]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Emma |last=Sanders|title=World Cup 2022: Uruguay 0-0 South Korea - nothing to separate teams in exciting goalless draw|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63657469|work=BBC Sport |date=24 November 2022 |access-date=24 November 2022 }}</ref> Pellistri scored his first international goal for Uruguay against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] in a friendly match on 5 June 2024 at [[Empower Field at Mile High]] in the United States. He also contributed an assist for [[Darwin Núñez]] in his hat-trick for a 4–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-06-06 |title=Uruguay goleó a México con un triplete de Darwin Núñez: reviví lo mejor – TyC Sports |url=https://www.tycsports.com/amistosos-de-selecciones/mexico-vs-uruguay-en-vivo-hora-donde-ver-y-formaciones-id588861.html |access-date=2024-06-06 |website=tycsports.com |language=es-AR}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, Pellistri was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
A [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], Pellistri has been praised highly for his agility, versatility, dribbling skills, technique, and strategic vision on the field. He has received praise from world-class footballers such as Diego Forlan and [[Juan Román Riquelme]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Turk |first=Alex |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/manchesterunited/news/riquelme-claims-there-arent-many-like-pellistri |title=South American great claims "there aren't many" like Facundo Pellistri |date=7 October 2020 |access-date=7 October 2020 |magazine=Sports Illustrated}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Fay |first=Richard |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/manchester-united-pellistri-latest-news-19050642 |title=What Diego Forlan has said about Man United signing Facundo Pellistri |date=5 October 2020 |access-date=7 October 2020 |publisher=Manchester Evening News}}</ref>

